Due to the overwhelming response of our runners, members, and partners, we
are broadening our fund-raising efforts to assist victims of the September
11 disaster.  To support New York Road Runners' goal of raising
$1 million, please send your donation to us and specify one of the
following groups:

September 11th Fund
This fund, set up by the United Way and The New York Community Trust, will
be used to help respond to the immediate and longer term needs of the
victims, their families, and  communities affected by the events of
September 11.

Twin Towers Fund
This fund is to assist the families of the members of the uniformed
services of the New York City Fire Department and its Emergency Medical
Services Command, the New York City Police Department, the Port Authority
of New York and New Jersey, and the New York State Office of Court
Administration and other offices who's employees lost their lives or were
injured in the September 11 tragedy. If resources permit, the  families of
other persons who lost their lives or were injured may also be included as
beneficiaries.

Please make your donation to one of the two funds and send to:

New York Road Runners
Att: (Name the Fund of your Choice)
9 East 89th Street
New York, NY 10128

If you choose to wire your contribution directly to the fund of your
choice, please send us a confirmation of your contribution so you can be
acknowledged in our total. For more information about how to help, please
click here (http://www.nyrrc.org/nyrrc/mar01/about/dedication.html)


